According to Dr. Christian Martel, Québec’s health care system is not effective enough to ensure the right to high quality palliative care before the transition to euthanasia is allowed.
Recently, she says, I saw a patient who spent 14 days in the E.R., in terrible pain, and no one took the necessary steps to ease them.
I'm afraid patients only want to die because they don't get adequate care.
