However, it must be noted that palliative care is not absolutely all-embracing in the fight against pain.
According to Elsie Monroe, the director of palliative care in the Palliative Care Society at the House of Greater Montreal, patients are not susceptible to pain treatment in 8% of cases.
At the very end of their lives, doctors often resort to palliative sedation, in which the patient sleeps until his death, either occasionally or permanently.
