I don't have another chance.
Only to convince politicians, journalists and the public and try to win them over so that we can get what we need.
Had I been elected President, there would have been no problem with a live television broadcast calling on the presidents of parliamentary parties to legitimize material and criminal responsibility for politicians, government officials, judges and prosecutors.
And if they refuse, they'll have to tell you why they don't want to.
If there is a strong person who speaks of abuse, then there can be pressure on the political scene.
Take a direct presidential election - it was a public pressure.
I'm telling you directly that I'm an amateur, not a genius or an intellectual.
I try to find allies to defend my beliefs and beliefs.
I'm just starting politics, and for my program, I'm gonna try to get the majority's support.
I'm trying to move things forward on my own; if that doesn't work out, I'll be done in six years, and I'll be back in the private sector.
It kind of sounds like Okamura's supposed to save the Czech Republic.
I'm no savior.
I know I'm the only one who's gonna do nothing, so I've bypassed a number of famous people with an offer to run for Senate.
I went to Radim Yanchure, he refused because of the heavy workload.
I also at least supported the ongoing investigation of journalist Jan Lorenzov, who discovered fraud with light fuel oil products.
I've put forward my candidacy because people are really dissatisfied, but now I feel like I'm on the scales.
Sixty per cent of the people did not go to the election, and most of those who went to the establishment did not.
There are only two of us independent in the Senate.
People have chosen the Senate in such a way that the changes will be difficult to implement.
Despite this, I will fight for my views, for example, for direct election of mayors and governors.
Are you thinking about the basis of your own party?
I haven't thought about it yet, because I don't have time to test the integrity of every potential supporter's past, and I don't have the money to do it.
There's no money for the presidential campaign, only 20,000 kroner in my transparent account.
You don't have any money?
You're talking about property declarations, and what's your own business with that?
Personal property is estimated at approximately 60 million.
I have a plot in Prague worth about 25 million, an apartment worth 10 million, another apartment worth 8 million, a collection of works of art worth about 10 million, an Aston Martin worth 3.5 million, and a Schcode Superb worth a million, and a few million more.
By the way, I had Aston-Martin because it was my boy's dream - I always liked James Bond, who drove, was gallant with women, and at the same time fought against scorn and lawlessness.
You drive Aston Martin, you own $60 million worth of property, and you don't have the money to campaign?
You say you want to change the republic, but you don't want to invest your own money in it.
